<font color="#FF0000">A MEMORIAL IS MADE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28  8:44:41 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
NO FLAGS FLEW THEN<br><br>
A chilly spring wind blew my skirt damply<br>
Against the back of your legs. Somewhere, cherry<br>
Blossoms bloomed in the night's wet air. We stood<br>
Outside a circle of floodlights but could<br>
Not look at the Washington Monuments's bright height.<br>
Machines splattered bullets, dimming camp lights,<br>
You said.  Crying children ran, and choppers,<br>
Beating the air, hovered like khaki angels<br>
Over carrion.  You gripped my hand until<br>
Bone touched bone, and we hung on, standing still,<br>
Hoping silence would stitch the nightmare closed:<br>
But chains clanged against the hollow flagpoles.<br>
And still the night wind makes those loose chains ring,<br>
As I lean into the shadows of that dark spring.<br><br>
                           
